David is mostly correct.  The latest message from HOSTMASTER announced
David's step (3), in which hosts which have full-qualified domain names
will have those names listed in the next version of HOSTS.TXT as the
primary name.  The old ".ARPA" names will be kept as a nickname.  Step
(5) is "futures" which as far as I'm concerned is uncontroversial.  I
am advocating the addition of step (1).

David is incorrect in his last paragraph, because the NIC message
clearly announced this would happen to all "domained" hosts and as such
this is an action by the NIC.  The controversy is only in the addition
of fully-qualified domain names at all and so this would be a one-time
event.  Once everybody's software is verified to run in this mode (e.g.
I BELIEVE TOPS-20 will work with these new names but I don't KNOW for a
fact it will) future domain name additions are uncontroversial.
